To the responsible
I have been asked to write to you regarding your mass surveillance investigation.
My name is Edward Joseph Snowden and I used to be contracted or contracted. through a direct position as a technical expert at the National Security Agency (NSA), the Central Intelligence Agency (CIA) and the United States Defense Intelligence Agency (DIA).
In the course of my employment in these institutions, I witnessed systematic violations of the law by my government, which led me to act out of moral duty.
As a result of the publication of these concerns, I faced a serious and ongoing incitement that forced me to leave my family and homeland.
I am currently living in exile and enjoying temporary asylum, which the Russian Federation grants me in accordance with international law.
I am encouraged by the response to my political action, both in the US and elsewhere.
Citizens around the world, and also senior officials - including the United States - have judged the revelations about a system of all-encompassing surveillance that is not accountable to anyone as a service to the public.
These spy revelations drew many proposals on new laws and guidelines aimed at the previously covert abuse of public trust.
The benefits for society from these findings are becoming increasingly clear; at the same time, the risks accepted have been visibly reduced.
Although the result of my efforts has been demonstrably positive, my government continues to treat dissent as a breach of allegiance and strives to criminalize and impose political expression.
Nevertheless, speaking the truth is not a crime.
I am confident that the United States Government, with the support of the international community, will adopt this detrimental stance.
I hope that, if the difficulties of this humanitarian situation are resolved, I will be able to participate appropriately and lawfully in the responsible clarification of the facts concerning the statements made in the media, in particular with regard to the truth and authenticity of the reports.
I look forward to a conversation with you in your country as soon as the situation is resolved and thank you for your efforts to uphold the international law that protects us all.
