Other bodies hope to be able to sell the concept of a suspicious public by equipping the devices with more features than with fewer.
In New York City, traffic officials want to develop a taxation device that can also be used to pay parking fees, insurance only has to be paid for kilometres driven and speed data is collected in real time from other vehicles, thanks to which motorists can avoid traffic jams.
